  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Maytag, Whirlpool's heavy-duty mass-market tier since 2006</h2>
    <p>Maytag Corporation was acquired by Whirlpool Corporation in 2006, making Maytag a sibling brand to Whirlpool mainstream, KitchenAid premium, JennAir luxury, Amana value, and Roper entry-tier within Whirlpool's North American appliance family. Maytag's positioning is mass-market heavy-duty, same tier as Whirlpool mainstream but with a distinct personality emphasizing heavier-duty build and the brand's signature 10-Year Limited Parts Warranty on select internal components. Parts infrastructure shares substantial commonality with Whirlpool mainstream, which translates to strong service parts availability through Whirlpool Corporation's North American distribution network.</p>
    <p>For LA service, common Maytag wall oven parts 1-3 day lead through Whirlpool distribution; specialty components 3-5 days. Maytag wall ovens under 10 years old may have warranty-covered parts on specific failure modes, we verify at diagnostic before quoting.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Maytag wall oven models we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Maytag 30" single built-in wall oven</h3><p>Mass-market heavy-duty single-cavity. Standard convection + self-clean. Service: bake/broil element, convection fan, control board, sensors, door hardware.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Maytag 30" double built-in wall oven</h3><p>Stacked dual-cavity. Upper + lower independent elements + sensors, shared primary control.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Maytag Commercial-Grade positioning</h3><p>Marketing emphasis on heavier-duty residential-spec build. Not commercial kitchen spec, residential service applies.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>10-Year Limited Parts Warranty</h3><p>Select components (motors, stainless cavity, designated major parts) covered for 10 years on original-purchaser ownership. Parts-only warranty; labor separate.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Whirlpool family parts commonality</h3><p>Bake elements, convection fan motors, many sensor + control variants interchange with Whirlpool mainstream + Amana value at comparable spec levels.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Self-clean pyrolytic cycle</h3><p>Standard self-clean on Maytag wall ovens. Door-lock motor + thermal sensor + cycle firmware service.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Common Maytag wall oven faults</h2>
    <p><b>Bake or broil element failure</b>, 8-12 year typical. $220-$380 per element. May be warranty-covered on units under 10 years.</p>
